comments: Ingram (NOP) establishes himself in Grimes' (NYK) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Hart (NYK) legally contests Jones's (NOP) jump shot attempt.
Ingram (NOP) delivers body contact to Barrett (NYK) and affects Barrett's (NYK) SQBR at the end of his drive before he gathers and enters his upward shooting motion.
Ingram (NOP) establishes himself in Grimes' (NYK) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Hartenstein (NYK) and Nance Jr. (NOP) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs off-ball.
As Ingram (NOP) makes a dribble move Hart (NYK) firms up and absorbs the marginal contact that occurs.
Hart (NYK) legally contests Ingram's (NOP) jump shot attempt.
Nance Jr (NOP) initiates the illegal contact, as he grabs Hartenstein's (NYK) arm and affects his ability to pursue the rebound.
Hartenstein (NYK) momentarily places a hand on Nance Jr.'s (NOP) lower body and marginal contact occurs as he rolls to the basket.
Jones (NOP) contests the jump shot attempt and avoids making contact with Quickley's (NYK) arm.
Hart (NYK) commits a take foul on McCollum (NOP).
Barrett (NYK) goes to, not through, Jones' (NOP) space and marginal contact occurs as Barrett (NYK) releases away at the end of the drive.

Nance Jr. (NOP) jumps towards Barrett (NYK to contest the driving shot attempt and marginal body contact occurs after the release of the shot.  The "high-five" contact to Barrett's hand is considered incidental.
